bowt.hand.impl

Class GuildCommandHandler

  • java.lang.Object
    • bowt.hand.impl.GuildCommandHandler
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    CommandHandler

    public class GuildCommandHandler
extends java.lang.Object
implements CommandHandler
    A default CommandHandler implementation which is meant for commands in normal guild channels.

    Example of usage

     GuildCommandHandler handler = new GuildCommandHandler(exampleGuildObject);
 
 Command cmd = new BaseCommand(new String[]{"help", "h"}, 
                              UserPermissions.USER);
 
 handler.addCommand(cmd);

    This code achieves that the handler will execute the help command whenever someone types 'prefix-h' or 'prefix-help' in a chat on 'exampleGuildObject'.

      • GuildCommandHandler

        public GuildCommandHandler()
        Creates a new instance that will handle Commands.

        Note
        An instance from this constructor should only be used to handle commands from private channels.

        Use GuildCommandHandler(GuildObject) to handle commands in normal guild channels.

        See Also:
        GuildCommandHandler(GuildObject), DefaultPrivateCommandHandler
